{"author":"RebarBotNava","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"clayish-basaltine-bug","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Context / Problem\n\nThe AWS Gerrit `LLM-Review` bot (`src/rebar/review_bot/`) makes billable LLM calls on\nevery patchset review but records **no token usage** in any retrievable form. Per-call token\nusage is computed by the runner (`_extract_usage` → `input_tokens`, `output_tokens`,\n`cache_read_tokens`, `cache_write_tokens`, `requests`; `src/rebar/llm/runner.py`) and attached\nas `result[\"_usage\"]`, but the review path discards the token fields: the code-review metrics\nassembler reads `_usage` only for the verifier **request count**\n(`src/rebar/llm/code_review/finalize.py:157`, `verify_requests`), and the voter never reads\nusage at all. The bot already publishes CloudWatch *error* counts via a best-effort boto3\npattern (`src/rebar/review_bot/voter.py:88-102`, `:145-165`), so there is an established seam\nto emit token counts the same way — it is simply not wired for usage.\n\nGoal: have the bot read `_usage` and emit token counts to CloudWatch.\n\n**Coverage scope (explicit).** This ticket captures the token usage that is already surfaced\non the review's **agent** step outputs — Pass-2 `verify` and Pass-3 `decide`\n(`finalize.py:143-162` already iterates these and reads their `_usage`). The Pass-1 **finder\nbatch** does NOT surface per-finder `_usage` on its step output\n(`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/production_batch_runner.py:168-177` emits `findings`/`criteria_count`\nbut no `_usage`; the shared `run_pass1` returns only `findings`,\n`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/pass1.py:548`), and threading finder usage through that shared\nplan-review path is a larger, riskier change. So the emitted totals are the review's\nagent-step token usage, labelled as such, and a follow-up ticket is filed (linked\n`discovered_from`) to surface Pass-1 finder usage for a complete total. This is strictly\nbetter than today's zero token visibility and does not misrepresent the number.\n\nEdit-set:\n- `src/rebar/llm/code_review/finalize.py`\n- `src/rebar/review_bot/voter.py`\n- *new* `tests/unit/test_review_bot_token_metrics.py`\n\n## Approach\n\n1. `finalize.py` `_attach_code_review_metrics`: in the existing `rec.steps` loop that already\n   reads `outputs[\"_usage\"]`, aggregate the token fields across **every succeeded step that\n   exposes `_usage`** (not just the verify request count). Add to `coverage[\"metrics\"]`:\n   `input_tokens`, `output_tokens`, `cache_read_tokens`, `cache_write_tokens`, and\n   `total_tokens` (= input + output). Keep `verify_requests` unchanged. This also enriches the\n   persisted `code_review` artifact (which serializes `coverage.metrics`), so the data is\n   retrievable both in CloudWatch and in the artifact. The addition is additive and tolerant of\n   steps without `_usage` (contributes 0).\n2. `voter.py`: add `_publish_token_usage_metrics(metrics: dict)` — best-effort boto3\n   `put_metric_data` to `Namespace=\"rebar/host\"`, one `MetricData` entry per token field\n   (`review_bot_llm_input_tokens`, `review_bot_llm_output_tokens`,\n   `review_bot_llm_cache_read_tokens`, `review_bot_llm_cache_write_tokens`,\n   `review_bot_llm_total_tokens`; `Unit: \"Count\"`), swallowing any ImportError/boto/credential\n   error exactly like `_publish_voter_error_metric` (`voter.py:88-102`). Also emit a greppable\n   `LLM_TOKEN_USAGE ` JSON line to stderr/journald for the reliable host-probe fallback,\n   mirroring the error markers. Call it after a **successful** vote (in `review_and_vote`, right\n   after the `voter_voted` emit, ~`voter.py:644-657`), reading the totals from\n   `decision[\"verdict\"][\"coverage\"][\"metrics\"]` (the verdict is threaded up at\n   `src/rebar/review_bot/adapter.py:219`). Best-effort: the vote is already cast, so emission\n   never fails the review (wrapped, swallowed, logged) — same contract as artifact emission.\n\nRejected: threading Pass-1 finder `_usage` through `run_pass1` now (shared plan-review path,\nsignature change, thread-pool aggregation) — deferred to the linked follow-up. Rejected a\nprocess-global `REBAR_USAGE_LOG`/accumulator to capture all calls — the bot reviews changes\nconcurrently, so a process-global sink would interleave usage across reviews.\n\n## Scope\n\n- Emits **token counts only** (input/output/cache/total tokens + the existing request count).\n  No dollar cost (no token→USD price table exists in the repo).\n- CloudWatch emission is **best-effort** and swallowed on any failure — identical fail-open\n  contract to the existing error-metric publishers; a metric failure never affects the vote.\n- Covers Pass-2 verify + Pass-3 decide agent-step usage (see Coverage scope above); Pass-1\n  finder usage is a linked follow-up.\n- No change to voting logic, thresholds, dedup, or the artifact schema beyond the additive\n  `coverage.metrics` token keys.\n\n## Testing\n\nNew `tests/unit/test_review_bot_token_metrics.py` (offline; no live LLM, no real AWS):\n- `finalize`: build a fake step-recorder (`rec.steps`) with agent steps carrying `_usage`\n  dicts and assert `_attach_code_review_metrics` sums `input_tokens`/`output_tokens`/\n  `cache_read_tokens`/`cache_write_tokens`/`total_tokens` into `coverage[\"metrics\"]`, and that a\n  record with no `_usage` yields zeros (tolerant). Mirrors the metrics assertions in\n  `tests/unit/test_code_review_fp_ledger.py` / `tests/unit/test_findings_finalize.py`.\n- `voter`: monkeypatch a fake `boto3` module capturing `put_metric_data` calls and assert\n  `_publish_token_usage_metrics({...})` emits the five named metrics with the right values to\n  `Namespace=\"rebar/host\"`; assert that when `boto3` import/credentials fail the call swallows\n  the error (returns without raising). Mirrors the boto3-absence tolerance the existing\n  publishers document (`voter.py:101`).\n- Optionally assert (via the existing `review_and_vote` test harness in\n  `tests/unit/test_review_bot.py`) that a successful vote invokes the token publisher with the\n  verdict's `coverage.metrics`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `_attach_code_review_metrics` adds `input_tokens`, `output_tokens`, `cache_read_tokens`,\n      `cache_write_tokens`, and `total_tokens` to `coverage[\"metrics\"]`, summed across all\n      `_usage`-bearing succeeded steps; verified by the finalize unit test asserting exact sums.\n- [ ] A step record with no `_usage` contributes 0 and never raises; verified by the tolerance\n      unit test.\n- [ ] `voter._publish_token_usage_metrics` emits exactly the five `review_bot_llm_*_tokens`\n      metrics to `Namespace=\"rebar/host\"` with `Unit=\"Count\"` and values from the passed\n      metrics dict; verified by the fake-boto3 unit test capturing `put_metric_data`.\n- [ ] `_publish_token_usage_metrics` swallows a boto3 import/credential/network failure without\n      raising; verified by the boto3-absence unit test.\n- [ ] `review_and_vote` calls the token publisher after a successful vote using\n      `decision[\"verdict\"][\"coverage\"][\"metrics\"]`; verified by the voter harness test (or an\n      equivalent direct assertion).\n- [ ] A follow-up ticket for Pass-1 finder token capture is created and linked\n      `discovered_from` this ticket.\n- [ ] `make lint`, `make typecheck`, and `make test` pass; `finalize.py` and `voter.py` stay\n      ≤ 800 LOC; the change lands via Gerrit with `Verified +1` and `LLM-Review +1`.","id":"fd71-a0a0-d9b0-4769","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Review bot: read _usage and emit token counts to CloudWatch"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784854949570847001,"uuid":"91fda1ca-5259-49a5-86b0-df4256d097fa"}